    <section>
        <title>About standard deviation outlier analysis</title>
        <para>The standard deviation outlier analysis provides a mechanism for revealing values that
            are numerically distant from the rest of the data. The analysis is based on the standard
            normal distribution. Outliers can occur by chance but often indicate a measurement error
            or a heavy-tailed distribution which leads to very high numbers. You should investigate
            measurement errors and try to correct them before you discard them from the
            analysis.</para>
        <para>
            <note>
                <para>Be
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170112T154953+0100" comment="Replace with &quot;it&apos;s not recommended&quot;?"?>cautious<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    to use tools or interpretations that assume a normal distribution for
                    heavy-tailed distributions.</para>
            </note>
        </para>
    </section>
